(160, 9786020676470, 'The Miracle of Oral Albumin : Natural Channa striata Extract', 'Cipto Kokadir', 30, 1, 8, '30 Jun 2024', '212 Halaman; 21 x 14 cm', 'In 1941, amidst the Pearl Harbor attack, a noteworthy revelation regarding the lifesaving capabilities of albumin came to light. Research on the benefits of albumin for human health continues to this day.\n\nIt was discovered that albumin can be found in an unexpected source: the snakehead fish, also known as Channa striata. The development of Channa striata as a source of albumin has opened the door to utilizing natural resources for albumin production.\n\nOnoiwa (Channa striata extract) has been used therapeutically at major hospitals, maternal and childrens hospitals, geriatric clinics, diabetes wards, cancer wards, cardio wards, endocrine wards, emergency wards, and many more. The low temperature extraction technology has resulted in highly effective albumin.\n\nNucleus Farma has intensively engaged in research with numerous universities both in Indonesia and abroad. Clinical experiences by multiple medical doctors with over 12.000 patients have confirmed the benefit of this nutrient-rich superfood, oral albumin.\n\nThis book, based on literature, presents a comprehensive explanation of albumin and its vital role in the human body. It is highly recommended for health practitioners, such as doctors, nurses, pharmacists, dietitians, and medical researchers, as well as anyone interested in studying albumin, oral albumin, and its benefits.\n\nAbout Author:\nCipto Kokadir is a scientist, an engineer, and a medical researcher. He graduated from the University of California at Berkeley, United States, with a BS magna cum laude (high honors) in double major Chemical Engineering and Materials Science Engineering. He attended graduate school in Engineering Management at Stanford University. He conducted research at Lawrence Livermore National Laboratory before starting the biotech nutraceutical company Nucleus Farma, an FDA-registered facility whose flagship product is Onoiwaa peptide preparation of Channa striata extract. He has received several awards and holds numerous patents in the biotechnology field.', '/storage/cover_buku/9786020676470.jpg', '2025-04-24 10:16:40', '2025-04-24 10:16:40'),
(161, 9786020678184, 'I\'m a Future Marine Biologist!', 'Manisha Nayak', 1, 1, 28, '4 Sep 2024', '56 Halaman; 15 x 22 cm', 'I\'M A FUTURE MARINE BIOLOGIST!\nDo male seahorses really give birth? Are corals plants or animals? Can sea stars regrow their limbs? Does an octopus have blue blood? Why does a puffer fish puff up?\nCurious to find out the answers to these questions? Join Sulin the sea star on an exciting journey and learn all about marine animals.\n\nSeri I\'m a Future Scientist (5 titles)\nI\'M A FUTURE WATER EXPERT!\nI\'M A FUTURE BOTANIST!\nI\'M A FUTURE ZOOLOGIST!\nI\'M A FUTURE ASTRONOMER!\nI\'M A FUTURE MARINE BIOLOGIST!\n\n*****\n\"I\'m a Future Marine Biologist!\" adalah buku yang dirancang khusus untuk membangkitkan minat anak-anak, terutama yang berusia 6-12 tahun, pada dunia biologi laut. Buku ini merupakan bagian dari seri \"Young Scientist\" yang populer di Singapura dan bertujuan untuk memperkenalkan konsep-konsep ilmiah dengan cara yang menyenangkan dan mudah dipahami.\n\n\nApa yang membuat buku ini menarik?\nCerita yang menarik: Buku ini disajikan dengan gaya bercerita yang engaging, sehingga anak-anak akan merasa seperti sedang mengikuti petualangan seorang calon ahli biologi laut.\n\nIlmu pengetahuan yang dikemas dengan menyenangkan: Konsep-konsep biologi laut yang kompleks, seperti siklus hidup makhluk laut, adaptasi, dan ekosistem, dijelaskan dengan bahasa yang sederhana dan dilengkapi dengan ilustrasi yang menarik.\n\nElemen Augmented Reality (AR): Fitur AR pada buku ini memungkinkan anak-anak untuk berinteraksi dengan konten buku secara lebih mendalam. Mereka bisa melihat makhluk laut dalam bentuk 3D, seolah-olah berada di dalam lautan.\n\nTopik yang beragam: Buku ini membahas berbagai topik menarik tentang biologi laut, mulai dari kehidupan sehari-hari makhluk laut hingga isu-isu konservasi.\n\nMemenuhi standar kurikulum: Materi dalam buku ini sesuai dengan standar kurikulum ilmu pengetahuan untuk anak usia sekolah dasar.', '/storage/cover_buku/9786020678184.jpg', '2025-04-24 10:16:40', '2025-04-24 10:16:40'),
(162, 9786020678290, 'Happy Learning Math: Abby the Anteater Feast on the Ants', 'Fynn Sor', 1, 1, 19, '4 Sep 2024', '32 Halaman; 21 x 26 cm', 'Abby the Anteater is upset that her mother eats more ants than her.\nFollow the anteaters eventful day at the grassland and learn to skip count by five and ten.\nRead fun facts about giant anteaters!\n\nJump start your childs advancement in numeracy with the Happy Learning\nMath series. Your child will delight in the fun stories about animals and\nencounter Math concepts, such as ordinal numbers, counting, skip counting,\naddition, subtraction and more.\n\nMaterials for interactive play and links to printables are also included, turning\neach book into a hands-on experiential learning tool. Fun Science facts are also\nweaved into each story to spark your childs curiosity about the world.This book comes with bonus fun and interactive elements to reinforce your childs learning of Math concepts!\n\nAbout Author:\nFynn is the founder of Happy Tot Shelf, a popular educational website about making learning fun and lively with hands- on activities for children. She is an author and a former Math and Science teacher. As she watched her children grow Fynn was constantly in awe at how they loved to learn. Determined to nurture their love for learning, she applied her passion and experience in education to create enriching learning activities for them. She shares these ideas, resources and tips with parents on Happy Tot Shelf so that they can raise happy learners too.\n\nFynn lives in Singapore with her husband, three children and three guinea pigs. Follow Fynn on Instagram @happytotshelf and her website www.happytotshell.com', '/storage/cover_buku/9786020678290.jpg', '2025-04-24 10:16:40', '2025-04-24 10:16:40'),
